## Problem

You just ran `squad init`. This item exists so you can practice the loop without
any real work at stake. Walk through it once and you'll know how the system
fits together.

## Context

The loop is: claim → work → tick → done. Every command is greppable from
`squad --help`. The item file you're reading right now is the durable
contract; the SQLite-backed claim is the live lock.

## Acceptance criteria

- [ ] Claim this item: `squad claim EXAMPLE-001 --intent "trying the loop"`
- [ ] Tick to confirm registration: `squad tick`
- [ ] Post a thought: `squad thinking "first squad loop"`
- [ ] Mark done with a one-line outcome: `squad done EXAMPLE-001 --summary "loop works"`
- [ ] Verify the file moved to `.squad/done/`
- [ ] Delete this file (it's served its purpose)

